OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FOutbreaks of
OL,6,Frain pushing eastwards, mostly light
OL,7,Fand patchy, but the odd heavier burst
OL,8,Fpossible over the hills. Turning more
OL,9,Fshowery overnight and milder than of
OL,10,Flate.
OL,11,
OL,12,CSunday:FBright spells and showers, the
OL,13,Fbest of the brightness expected during
OL,14,Fthe morning. The showers could be
OL,15,Fheavy, perhaps the odd rumble of
OL,16,Fthunder. Moderate westerly winds.
OL,17,
OL,18,COutlook for Monday to Wednesday:FMainly
OL,19,Fdry and bright on Monday with early
OL,20,Fshowers dying out. Rain or showers on
OL,21,FTuesday and Wednesday, heavy at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
